## Why This Redirect Exists

Wikipedia is littered with these digital breadcrumbs. Some exist because people make typos (shocking, I know). Others exist because alternate spellings or historical names might lead someone astray. This one exists purely because of a **miscapitalization**.

It's a common error. People often type "iron age" in lowercase, perhaps thinking it's a generic descriptor rather than a formal, defined historical period. They're wrong, of course. The [Iron Age](/Iron_Age) is a specific archaeological and historical era following the [Bronze Age](/Bronze_Age), characterized by the widespread use of [iron](/iron) or [steel](/steel). It's not just any old "age" that happens to have iron in it.

So, this redirect is a necessary evil, a gentle nudge to correct the misguided and the typo-prone.

